This paper focuses on comparing different types of recurrent units in recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for sequence modeling tasks such as polyphonic music modeling and speech signal modeling. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and signal processing (cs.SD) due to the focus on speech signal modeling. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL) due to the use of RNNs for language modeling.
